    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-02-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-02-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="831"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d831">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hardy</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-02-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 13, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 194.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your telegram of the 10th instant.</p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                <p>I immediately called upon the minister for foreign affairs at his house and
                    brought your suggestion to his notice. * * * He promised to bring the subject
                    before the council of ministers and to inform me at once of the result. Three
                    days having passed without information, I called at the ministry to-day, and
                    after some conversation in which it was apparent that the minister’s view as
                    above expressed had been confirmed, he requested me to inform you that for the
                    present His Majesty’s Government would not take any action beyond its
                    declaration of neutrality; that to suggest the recognition by the belligerents
                    of the neutrality of China might not seem to be in strict <pb facs="0895"
                        n="807" xml:id="pg_807"/> conformity with the duties of Spain as a neutral,
                    and that for the present Spain would await the action of the interested
                    powers.</p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Arthur S. Hardy.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
